{"id":"2208.04612","submitter":"Andrey Pikelner","authors":"Alexander Bednyakov, Andrey Pikelner","title":"Six-loop anomalous dimension of the $\\phi^Q$ operator in the $O(N)$\n  symmetric model","comments":"results in ancillary files","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.106.076015","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th cond-mat.stat-mech hep-ph","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  A technique of large-charge expansion provides a novel opportunity for\ncalculation of critical dimensions of operators $\\phi^Q$ with fixed charge $Q$.\nIn the small-coupling regime the polynomial structure of the anomalous\ndimensions can be fixed from a number of direct perturbative calculations for a\nfixed $Q$. At the six-loop level one needs to include new diagrams that\ncorrespond to operators with five or more legs. The latter never appeared\nbefore in scalar-theory calculations. Here we show how to compute the anomalous\ndimension of the operator $\\phi^{Q=5}$ at the six-loop order. In combination\nwith results for operators with $Q<5$, which are extracted from the six-loop\nbeta-functions for general scalar theory, and with predictions from the\nlarge-charge expansion, our calculation allows us to derive the answer for\ngeneral-$Q$ anomalous dimensions. At the critical point resummation in three\ndimensions enables us to compare the critical exponents with results of\nMonte-Carlo simulations and large-$N$ predictions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Aug 2022 09:07:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
