em from the one we see today. Therefore, it\nseems unlikely that Phobos and Deimos are split directly from a single\nancestral moon.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Aug 2022 14:13:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 22 Aug 2022 08:28:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-23"}
